  STAGED DRAFT — splynek.app v3.0 landing.
  =========================================
  Generated 2026-05-28 alongside the direct-sale launch package.
  NOT YET DEPLOYED.

  Before deploying:
    1. Maintainer completes Phase A2 of MAINTAINER-LAUNCH-CHECKLIST.md
       (LemonSqueezy product setup).
    2. Search this file for `LEMONSQUEEZY_CHECKOUT_URL` and replace
       with the live checkout URL (with ?coupon=LAUNCH1 for the
       first 30 days).
    3. Swap into place:
         mv docs/index.html docs/index.v2.0.1.html.archived
         mv docs/index.v3.0.html.draft docs/index.html
         git add docs/ && git commit -m "Landing → v3.0"
         git push        # GitHub Pages / Cloudflare auto-deploys
    4. Verify https://splynek.app/ shows the new hero + v3.0 badge.
-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover">
<title>Splynek — Trust Watcher for your Mac</title>
<meta name="description" content="Splynek tells you when the apps you use change their privacy policies or terms. Daily diff of Privacy Policies + ToS. Push notifications on your iPhone. 100% local detection.">
<meta property="og:title" content="Splynek — Trust Watcher for your Mac">
<meta property="og:description" content="Daily diff of Privacy Policies + Terms of Service for popular apps. 100% local. Push to your iPhone the moment something changes.">
<meta property="og:image" content="https://splynek.app/icon-1024.png">
<meta property="og:type" content="website">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://splynek.app/">
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
<meta name="theme-color" content="#0B1128">
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="icon-256.png">
<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="icon-256.png">
<style>
  :root {
    color-scheme: light dark;
    --bg:         #0B1128;
    --bg2:        #11183A;
    --panel:      #151C36;
    --panel-lift: #1A2145;
    --border:     rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    --border-lift: rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
    --text:       #ECEFF9;
    --text-dim:   #C9CEE3;
    --muted:      #8891B0;
    --accent:     #5ADCA5;
    --accent-dk:  #2FBC85;
    --gold:       #F5C16C;
    --purple:     #B48CFF;
    --pink:       #FF9BD2;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
  body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Text",
                 system-ui, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 1100px 700px at 50% -10%, rgba(90, 220, 165, 0.12) 0%, transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 900px 600px at 10% 40%,   rgba(180, 140, 255, 0.08) 0%, transparent 55%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 900px 600px at 90% 70%,   rgba(255, 155, 210, 0.06) 0%, transparent 55%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg2) 0%, var(--bg) 50%, var(--bg) 100%);
    background-attachment: fixed;
    color: var(--text);
    min-height: 100vh;
    line-height: 1.55;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  code {
    font-family: "SF Mono", ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.92em;
  }
  main { max-width: 1040px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

  nav.top {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 20px 0 12px;
  }
  nav.top .logo {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
    font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  nav.top .logo img { width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 6px; }
  nav.top .links { display: flex; gap: 22px; font-size: 14px; }
  nav.top .links a { color: var(--text-dim); }
  nav.top .links a:hover { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }

  header.hero {
    padding: 72px 0 56px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  header.hero .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(245, 193, 108, 0.12);
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  header.hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6.5vw, 68px);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.02;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  header.hero h1 .accent { color: var(--accent); }
  header.hero p.lede {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto 28px;
  }
  header.hero .cta-row {
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  header.hero .note {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #0B1128;
    border: none;
    padding: 13px 22px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14.5px;
    transition: background 100ms ease, transform 80ms ease;
  }
  .btn:hover { background: var(--accent-dk); text-decoration: none; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .btn.ghost {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-lift);
  }
  .btn.ghost:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }

  section {
    padding: 56px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  section:first-of-type { border-top: 0; }
  section h2 {
    font-size: 30px;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  section h2 .accent { color: var(--accent); }
  section p.section-lede {
    font-size: 16.5px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
  }

  .three-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
  }
  .three-col .card {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 22px 22px 24px;
    transition: border-color 120ms ease, transform 120ms ease;
  }
  .three-col .card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-lift);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .three-col .card .icon {
    width: 36px; height: 36px;
    background: rgba(90, 220, 165, 0.12);
    color: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 9px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .three-col .card .icon.gold   { background: rgba(245, 193, 108, 0.12); color: var(--gold); }
  .three-col .card .icon.purple { background: rgba(180, 140, 255, 0.12); color: var(--purple); }
  .three-col .card .icon.pink   { background: rgba(255, 155, 210, 0.12); color: var(--pink); }
  .three-col .card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-size: 17px;
  }
  .three-col .card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .tile-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(190px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .tile-grid .tile {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 18px;
  }
  .tile-grid .tile h4 {
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    font-size: 14.5px;
  }
  .tile-grid .tile p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .tile-grid .tile .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(180, 140, 255, 0.14);
    color: var(--purple);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  pre.code {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    font-family: "SF Mono", ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    overflow-x: auto;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }
  pre.code .c { color: var(--muted); }
  pre.code .k { color: var(--accent); }

  ul.changelog {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 10px 24px;
  }
  ul.changelog li {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  ul.changelog li .badge {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    background: rgba(90, 220, 165, 0.14);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 10px;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }
  ul.changelog li .badge.fix { background: rgba(245, 193, 108, 0.14); color: var(--gold); }

  .privacy-note {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 26px 28px;
  }
  .privacy-note p { margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 15px; }
  .privacy-note p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .privacy-note p strong { color: var(--text); }

  details.faq {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  details.faq summary {
    padding: 16px 20px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--text);
    list-style: none;
  }
  details.faq summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  details.faq summary::after {
    content: "+";
    float: right;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 18px;
  }
  details.faq[open] summary::after { content: "−"; }
  details.faq .a {
    padding: 0 20px 16px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 14.5px;
  }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    padding: 28px 0 56px;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }
  footer .links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; gap: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  footer a { color: var(--text-dim); }
  footer a:hover { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .three-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    ul.changelog { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    header.hero { padding-top: 48px; }
    section { padding: 40px 0; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<main>

  <nav class="top">
    <a class="logo" href="/">
      <img src="icon-256.png" alt="Splynek">
      <span>Splynek</span>
    </a>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="#features">Features</a>
      <a href="/trustwatcher/">Trust catalog</a>
      <a href="#download">Download</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Splynek/splynek">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <header class="hero">
    <span class="badge">v3.0 — out today</span>
    <h1>
      Splynek tells you when the apps you use<br>
      <span class="accent">change their privacy policies.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Daily diff of Privacy Policies + Terms of Service for the
      apps you have installed. Push to your iPhone the moment
      something changes. 100% local — no servers, no accounts,
      no telemetry.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row" id="download">
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/Splynek/splynek/releases/latest">
        Download for Mac → v3.0
      </a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/trustwatcher/">
        See what's watched
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="note">macOS 13.0+ · ~32 MB · Free tier MIT. Pro <strong>$24 launch week</strong> · $29 thereafter · lifetime. Buy at <a href="/pro/">splynek.app/pro</a>.</p>
  </header>

  <section id="features">
    <h2>A whole product. <span class="accent">$24 launch week. $29 lifetime.</span></h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      Splynek Pro is one purchase that covers every Mac you own.
      No account. No subscription. The licence is a signed file
      you double-click — we never see your email.
      No "Premium Plus" tier, no seat counting, no annual
      renewal.
    </p>
    <div class="three-col">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon">🔔</div>
        <h3>Trust Watcher</h3>
        <p>
          Daily SHA-256 diff of public Privacy Policies and Terms
          of Service for 12 seeded popular apps (and growing via
          community PR). Material changes become alerts on your
          Mac and push notifications on your iPhone.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon gold">🛡</div>
        <h3>Sovereignty Migrate</h3>
        <p>
          Guided one-click swap from a US-controlled app to a
          European or open-source alternative. Per-step
          confirmation; the original app stays put unless you
          uninstall it manually.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon purple">🔑</div>
        <h3>API tokens for power users</h3>
        <p>
          Mint persistent named tokens for Raycast, Alfred,
          BetterTouchTool, shell scripts. Two scopes (read-only
          / read+write). Revoke any time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Every Pro feature, on your <span class="accent">iPhone too.</span></h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      The free Splynek Companion app on the App Store pairs with
      your Mac and surfaces every Pro feature on the phone. Same
      purchase covers both — same licence file activates Pro on the iPhone Companion when Apple clears that queue.
    </p>
    <div class="tile-grid">
      <div class="tile">
        <span class="pill">App Intent</span>
        <h4>Hey Siri, send to Splynek</h4>
        <p>Hands-free URL submission from anywhere on iOS.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <span class="pill">Live data</span>
        <h4>Insights tab</h4>
        <p>Sovereignty, Trust, Trust Watcher + Recent History from your default Mac.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <span class="pill">Glance</span>
        <h4>Home-screen Widget</h4>
        <p>Sovereignty score as a hero number, traffic-light tinted.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <span class="pill">Automate</span>
        <h4>Geo-fence</h4>
        <p>Auto-pause downloads when you leave home, auto-resume when you arrive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <span class="pill">Watch</span>
        <h4>Apple Watch</h4>
        <p>Tap-to-pause complications and quick-actions for the paired Mac.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>If you can write a <span class="accent">curl</span>, you can drive Splynek.</h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      Splynek's HTTP API is token-gated and runs on your LAN.
      The same surface that powers the Raycast extension,
      Alfred workflow, and bash cookbook is open to every
      shell script you'll ever write.
    </p>
<pre class="code"><span class="c"># Queue a URL from anywhere on your LAN</span>
curl -X POST -d '{"url":"https://example.com/file.iso"}' \
  "http://mac.local:<span class="k">PORT</span>/splynek/v1/api/queue?t=$SPLYNEK_TOKEN"

<span class="c"># Read your Sovereignty score</span>
curl -s "http://mac.local:<span class="k">PORT</span>/splynek/v1/api/sovereignty/summary?t=$SPLYNEK_TOKEN" \
  | jq '.score'</pre>
    <div class="three-col">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon purple">⚡</div>
        <h3>Raycast</h3>
        <p>5 commands (Submit URL, Active Downloads, Sovereignty Score, Pause All, Resume All). Token-aware via Raycast preferences.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon">🖥</div>
        <h3>CLI cookbook</h3>
        <p>Bash wrapper with 9 subcommands plus a curl/jq recipe book — pause-on-DND, daily-Sovereignty-cron, geo-trigger-via-iOS-Shortcut.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon pink">🤖</div>
        <h3>MCP server</h3>
        <p>Splynek speaks Model Context Protocol over JSON-RPC. Wire it into Claude Desktop, opt-in via Settings.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What's new in <span class="accent">v3.0</span></h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      The biggest Splynek ever — and the first shipped direct,
      outside the Mac App Store.  Apple's MAS re-review queue
      crossed 30+ days with no human reply; the product was
      finished, so v3.0 ships from splynek.app via notarized DMG +
      Sparkle auto-update + LemonSqueezy for Pro.
    </p>
    <ul class="changelog">
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Four lifecycle tabs.</strong> Discover · Download · My Apps · Coordinate. Floating-card sidebar with traffic-lights inside the pane (the Apple TV.app look).</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Trust Watcher</strong> (Pro) — daily SHA-256 diff of Privacy Policies + ToS for installed apps. Material changes show up in a dedicated inbox.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Sovereignty Migrate Wizard</strong> (Pro) — guided one-click swap from a paid US-controlled app to an EU or open-source alternative, with per-step confirmation.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Browser Accelerator.</strong> Chrome + Safari WebExtensions redirect large downloads + HLS manifests through Splynek's bonded multi-interface fetch.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>yt-dlp swallow.</strong> Splynek dispatches to your installed yt-dlp for YouTube / Twitch / Instagram / TikTok / X / Vimeo / Bilibili.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>File Witness</strong> — every completed download gets an Ed25519-signed receipt. Standalone CLI verifier ships alongside.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Unbreakable Resume.</strong> Path-flip pause/resume with sidecar continuity. Curated mirror failover for the major Linux distros.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Fleet 2.0.</strong> LAN peer cache with auto-join + household swarm token.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Direct-sale activation:</strong> buy → email <code>.splynekkey</code> → double-click → done. No phone-home, no account, Ed25519-signed offline verification.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>Sparkle auto-update</strong> from splynek.app/appcast.xml. "Check for Updates…" in the application menu.</span></li>
      <li><span class="badge">New</span><span><strong>L10n:</strong> 948 strings × 5 locales (pt-PT · es · fr · de · it), 100% coverage.</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="section-lede" style="margin-top: 1.2em;">
      <strong>iPhone Companion is built, tested, and waiting on
      Apple's iOS App Store queue.</strong>  Same bottleneck.  When
      it clears, every Pro buyer gets it as a free v3.1 update —
      Share Extension, Live Activity download progress, Trust
      Watcher push notifications, home-screen widget, App Intents.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>One screenshot. <span class="accent">Three lines.</span></h2>
    <p class="section-lede">Privacy through transparency.</p>
    <div class="privacy-note">
      <p>
        We don't know how much you use Splynek. We know you use
        it because we shipped a thing. The local engagement
        counters live in
        <code>~/Library/Application Support/Splynek/engagement.json</code>
        — you read the same file we'd read. We don't aggregate it.
        We don't transmit it. We don't have a server.
      </p>
      <p><strong>No telemetry.</strong> Ever.</p>
      <p><strong>No accounts.</strong> Pro is a signed <code>.splynekkey</code> file you double-click; we never see your email except via the LemonSqueezy purchase record (which they manage, not us).</p>
      <p><strong>No cloud sync of your downloads.</strong> Everything stays on your Macs + your iPhone.</p>
      <p><strong>CloudKit relay</strong> uses your <em>own</em> private iCloud database. Apple is the transport; Splynek never sees the records.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>Does Splynek work on macOS 13?</summary>
      <div class="a">Yes. Minimum target is macOS 13.0. Some optional features (widget container backgrounds, certain App Intents) need macOS 14+.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>What's the difference between Splynek (free) and Splynek Pro?</summary>
      <div class="a">Free includes the full download engine — multi-interface HTTP, BitTorrent v2, browser extension, App Intents. Pro adds Trust Watcher, Sovereignty Migrate Wizard, AI Concierge, AI history search, scheduled downloads, mobile dashboard, API tokens, and fleet beyond 2 devices.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>How can I trust the Trust Watcher catalog?</summary>
      <div class="a">The catalog is hand-curated, MIT-licensed, and grows via public pull request. Every URL points to the vendor's <em>own</em> canonical Privacy Policy or ToS page — linked from their site footer or App Store listing. See <a href="/trustwatcher/">the public catalog</a> for the current list.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>Will my downloads be visible to anyone else on my Wi-Fi?</summary>
      <div class="a">Only via the LAN HTTP API, which is token-gated. The token lives in your keychain; you choose who has it. Free tier defaults to loopback-only (the HTTP server only binds to 127.0.0.1). Pro opens it to the LAN so the iPhone Companion can reach it.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>Is Trust+ a thing yet?</summary>
      <div class="a">Not yet. We're collecting interest via the in-app Engagement gate. If 90+ days of local engagement counters show real demand we may launch a $9/yr Trust+ tier with weekly catalog refreshes and an acquisition radar. Your existing Pro license keeps everything you have today.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>How do I revoke API tokens?</summary>
      <div class="a">Settings → API tokens → Revoke. External clients using that token immediately get 401.</div>
    </details>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/trustwatcher/">Trust catalog</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Splynek/splynek/releases">All releases</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Splynek/splynek">GitHub</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Splynek/splynek/blob/main/MCP_SETUP.md">MCP setup</a>
